(2) A levy assessment officer or an assistant levy assessment officer may grant partial or complete exemption from the payment of levy , either generally or in respect of any year, to any person who, in his opinion, is unable to pay the amount of levy due from him by reason of poverty arising from either— (a) old age; (b) infirmity; or (c) other good cause. Any exemption from the payment of levy granted under this subsection may be revoked by the levy assessment officer or an assistant levy assessment officer at any time for good cause.
