(2) For the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this section, a levy assessment officer or assistant levy assessment officer — (a) may take evidence on oath and for that purpose is hereby empowered to administer oaths; (b) may require any person to attend at some reasonable time and place as a witness and give evidence or to produce any document in his possession or power which relates to the assessment of a leviable person ; (c) may by notice require any employer, whether within or without the area, to prepare and deliver to him within the time limited by the notice a return containing— (i) the names and places of residence of all persons employed by him; (ii) the payments made to those persons in respect of that employment during any period not exceeding twelve months.
