(3) The office of a member shall be vacated— (a) upon his death; (b) if he is adjudged bankrupt; (c) upon the expiry of one month's notice in writing of his intention to resign his office given by him to the levy authority ; (d) if he becomes mentally or physically incapable of performing his duties as a member; (e) if he is convicted of an offence and sentenced to imprisonment without the option of a fine; (f) three years after the date of his appointment: Provided that a member retiring under paragraph (f) shall be eligible for reappointment.
